  "notes": "Let’s make this real with an example of how agentic tooling and the Cloud Accelerate Factory work together with your team on an actual modernization journey.\n\nThis journey started with a traditional monolithic application running on legacy infrastructure. The Cloud Accelerate Factory began by assessing the application and environment — looking at code structure & dependencies, to create a modernization plan moving to a microservices‑based architecture aligned with the customer’s standards.\n\nFrom there, the Factory drove the modernization loop —refactoring and upgrading application code, containerizing services, and validating changes against cloud native capabilities. Changes were reviewed and approved by the customer’s development team as they progressed, while the Factory managed execution, ran the iterations, and maintained delivery momentum.\n\nIn parallel, the Factory created repeatable infrastructure‑as‑code templates and deployment patterns, tailored to the customer’s environment so each environment started from a consistent, governed baseline.\nThe outcome was measurable acceleration: Faster environment readiness, less rework during reviews, and reusable patterns that could be applied across the rest of the portfolio.\n\nThis is joint delivery from discovery to production — Tools and agents can accelerate tasks. The Factory helps you turn that into a repeatable delivery motion — with expert capacity, structured execution, and reusable automation — so you can modernize faster and at scale."
